DEPUTY president and the South African National Aids Council (Sanac) chairperson, Cyril Ramaphosa, will today lead the launch of a dialogue series on gender-based violence and related issues in Soshanguve, Pretoria.The dialogues comes hot on the heels of a spike in gender-based violence in the country that has hogged international headlines.Topics ranging from gender-based violence, substance abuse HIV testing among others will come under sharp focus at the series of dialogues targeted at boys and men.Minister of Women in the Presidency Susan Shabangu, veteran South African actor and founder of AfriMan Rising Sello Maake Ka Ncube, civil society, and religious leaders are among those who will attend the launch.The dialogue series is expected to be rolled out to other parts of the country following the launch in Soshanguve. It comes amid a shocking number of high profile cases of gender-based violence and femicide cases in the country.Most recent video footage of Deputy Minister of Higher Education and Training Mduduzi Manana assaulting a woman at the Cubana night club surfaced sparking outrage. 701478TNA Reporter 